WEBVTT

1
00:02:20.988 --> 00:02:24.557
You know. I thought to
maybe drive up to the town.

2
00:02:24.657 --> 00:02:26.312
You want something?

3
00:02:26.412 --> 00:02:28.412
No.

4
00:02:58.526 --> 00:03:00.526
Hunter?

5
00:03:01.174 --> 00:03:04.999
Who knew they would
travel in pairs. I think.

6
00:03:06.954 --> 00:03:08.954
Come.

7
00:03:09.788 --> 00:03:11.788
Come on.

8
00:03:11.802 --> 00:03:13.802
What's going on?

9
00:03:18.539 --> 00:03:20.321
You have a gun?

10
00:03:20.421 --> 00:03:22.546
Why would you have a gun?

11
00:03:31.734 --> 00:03:33.051
Jack.

12
00:03:33.151 --> 00:03:35.151
Jack.

13
00:03:46.712 --> 00:03:48.712
Jack.

14
00:03:56.102 --> 00:03:58.102
Is he dead?

15
00:04:01.193 --> 00:04:07.137
Jack.
- Go to the house and call the police.

16
00:04:07.348 --> 00:04:09.348
Go.

17
00:06:52.362 --> 00:06:54.140
Yeah?
- It's Jack.

18
00:06:54.240 --> 00:06:56.008
I'm here.

19
00:06:56.108 --> 00:06:58.925
What do you mean 'here'?
- Rome.

20
00:07:02.902 --> 00:07:05.306
There is a bar near the main station.

21
00:07:05.406 --> 00:07:09.160
Cafe di Ghetto. Wait there.

22
00:08:04.235 --> 00:08:06.425
Jack.
- Papo.

23
00:08:07.740 --> 00:08:09.740
It's been a while.

24
00:08:13.332 --> 00:08:14.692
Who was the girl?

25
00:08:14.792 --> 00:08:19.381
A friend.
- A friend?

26
00:08:21.050 --> 00:08:23.050
Those were Swedes.

27
00:08:24.389 --> 00:08:28.299
I'm working on that.
It's gonna take some time.

28
00:08:28.873 --> 00:08:30.873
Did she set you up?

29
00:08:31.482 --> 00:08:34.032
She had nothing to do with it.

30
00:08:35.863 --> 00:08:37.863
Pity.

31
00:08:40.139 --> 00:08:41.605
You can't stay here.

32
00:08:41.705 --> 00:08:47.060
I made arrangements for you to leave
town while I sort this out.

33
00:08:50.675 --> 00:08:54.670
Take a right outside the
bar. Then second left.

34
00:08:54.744 --> 00:09:00.354
Near Magenta you'll find dark blue
Fiat Tempra with Pescara plates.

35
00:09:02.150 --> 00:09:06.230
I've marked small town on the map.
Castelvecchio.

36
00:09:07.574 --> 00:09:11.059
Stay there. Lay low till you get my call.

37
00:09:11.956 --> 00:09:13.956
Don't talk to anyone.

38
00:09:16.441 --> 00:09:18.323
And above all.

39
00:09:18.423 --> 00:09:20.888
Don't make any friends. Jack.

40
00:09:21.761 --> 00:09:23.761
You used to know that.

41
00:15:06.412 --> 00:15:08.412
'Giorno.

42
00:15:09.437 --> 00:15:11.437
Hello...

43
00:15:12.986 --> 00:15:15.280
Where are you from?
- I?

44
00:15:15.696 --> 00:15:16.847
Ah. you're an American.

45
00:15:16.947 --> 00:15:19.498
Yes. 'A American.'
- Not 'A American '.

46
00:15:19.598 --> 00:15:20.812
but' an American.'

47
00:15:20.912 --> 00:15:22.912
L'americano.

48
00:16:03.472 --> 00:16:06.084
Can I help you?
- I'm not good with machines...

49
00:16:06.184 --> 00:16:08.394
Are you an American?
- Yes.

50
00:16:08.897 --> 00:16:11.400
Speak Italian?
- A little.

51
00:16:12.131 --> 00:16:15.050
On vacation?
- A working vacation.

52
00:16:16.198 --> 00:16:19.683
Do you work?
What kind of job do you have?

53
00:16:20.580 --> 00:16:22.045
I am a photographer.

54
00:16:22.145 --> 00:16:24.145
Take pictures
- Yes.

55
00:16:24.231 --> 00:16:29.550
What kind of photos?
- Pictures of architecture. landscape.

56
00:16:29.760 --> 00:16:31.642
People?
- No people.

57
00:16:31.742 --> 00:16:34.558
Just publication for magazines.

58
00:16:34.871 --> 00:16:37.791
Magazines? Which magazines?

59
00:16:38.104 --> 00:16:42.173
Different ones. Casa Editrice
- Okay.

60
00:16:42.591 --> 00:16:44.785
You must share a glass of wine with me.

61
00:16:44.885 --> 00:16:47.180
Come tonight.
- I can't. no.

62
00:16:47.387 --> 00:16:50.208
You want to know the truth about Abruzzo?

63
00:16:50.308 --> 00:16:52.603
The priest sees everything.

64
00:17:51.020 --> 00:17:53.731
Yeah?
- It's Jack.

65
00:17:55.191 --> 00:17:58.014
You don't answer the cell I gave you.

66
00:17:58.114 --> 00:18:00.409
I'm not good with machines.

67
00:18:01.242 --> 00:18:04.472
You don't make this easy for me. Jack.

68
00:18:04.684 --> 00:18:06.684
Gotta job for you.

69
00:18:06.771 --> 00:18:11.701
It's a custom fit. You don't
even have to pull the trigger.

70
00:18:12.717 --> 00:18:14.717
I'll think about it.

71
00:18:29.093 --> 00:18:31.983
The quality of the brandy is good.

72
00:18:33.685 --> 00:18:35.685
Smooth.

73
00:18:36.395 --> 00:18:40.050
The only good thing to
come from the French.

74
00:18:51.834 --> 00:18:56.319
You study our history?
- No.

75
00:18:59.554 --> 00:19:05.603
You come to Italy to make a guidebook
and you don't care about history?

76
00:19:07.899 --> 00:19:11.550
I take pictures.
- Of course.

77
00:19:13.949 --> 00:19:15.949
You're American.

78
00:19:17.808 --> 00:19:23.442
You think you can escape history.
You live for the present.

79
00:19:24.902 --> 00:19:26.902
I try to. Father.

80
00:20:52.420 --> 00:20:53.677
Hello...

81
00:20:53.777 --> 00:20:58.262
I would like this cheese...
- A wheel of Pecorino?

82
00:20:58.576 --> 00:21:00.974
Okey. immediately. 12 Euros.

83
00:21:09.736 --> 00:21:11.736
Here.
- Thank you.

84
00:21:16.412 --> 00:21:18.412
Here is the change.

85
00:21:19.438 --> 00:21:22.255
Thanks.
- And I thank you.

86
00:21:34.772 --> 00:21:38.109
Thanks.
- You're welcome.

87
00:21:42.910 --> 00:21:45.203
Your coffee.
- Thank you.

88
00:21:46.559 --> 00:21:50.419
What you want. sir?
- Bring me an americano.

89
00:21:50.523 --> 00:21:52.523
In a minute.

90
00:21:55.217 --> 00:21:58.137
I am Edward.
- Mathilda.

91
00:22:08.048 --> 00:22:11.594
Range?
- 150 to 175 meters.

92
00:22:12.638 --> 00:22:16.705
Time?
- 5 seconds. 7 at the most.

93
00:22:17.644 --> 00:22:19.940
Target?
- One.

94
00:22:20.878 --> 00:22:22.966
Firing rate?
- Rapid.

95
00:22:24.633 --> 00:22:28.701
Magazine capacity?
- Large. Preferably a 556.

96
00:22:29.223 --> 00:22:31.837
The weapon must be
fairly light and compact.

97
00:22:31.937 --> 00:22:33.088
How compact?

98
00:22:33.188 --> 00:22:35.188
As compact as possible.

99
00:22:36.316 --> 00:22:39.138
What. an automatic weapon to
fit inside of a woman's purse?

100
00:22:39.238 --> 00:22:42.163
A small vanity case would be permissible.

101
00:22:42.263 --> 00:22:45.238
Small briefcase should be possible.

102
00:22:45.391 --> 00:22:47.791
Noise?
- Silencer.

103
00:22:48.417 --> 00:22:50.613
I can only give you a supressor.

104
00:22:50.713 --> 00:22:55.643
It will dampen the decibels
and dislocate the sound source.

105
00:22:55.718 --> 00:22:57.600
Reduce the muzzle flash.

106
00:22:57.700 --> 00:22:59.550
I can't make you silent but I can make you...

107
00:22:59.650 --> 00:23:01.879
...invisible as long as you're
willing to lose the range.

108
00:23:01.979 --> 00:23:03.979
2 o'clock.

109
00:23:05.942 --> 00:23:09.682
Light blue shirt. Sunglasses.
Is he with you?

110
00:23:12.096 --> 00:23:13.770
I didn't see him.

111
00:23:13.870 --> 00:23:15.870
In any case I'm alone.

112
00:23:18.459 --> 00:23:21.349
Your Coffee. American.
- Thank you.

113
00:23:25.969 --> 00:23:29.029
I can accept a slight loss of range.

114
00:23:30.143 --> 00:23:33.544
You want a weapon with a
firing capacity of a...

115
00:23:33.644 --> 00:23:36.614
...sub-machine gun with the range of a rifle.

116
00:23:36.714 --> 00:23:38.714
Can you do it?

117
00:25:50.757 --> 00:25:56.285
Clark. A package.
- Clark. Of course.

118
00:28:50.385 --> 00:28:52.385
I'm Clara.

119
00:29:08.014 --> 00:29:10.413
Thanks. See you tonight.

120
00:29:56.624 --> 00:29:59.341
All the sheep in my flock are dear to me.

121
00:29:59.441 --> 00:30:02.331
But some are dearer than the most.

122
00:30:02.674 --> 00:30:06.074
Especially those that have lost the way.

123
00:30:06.324 --> 00:30:10.184
Fabio. mechanic.
Car doctor.

124
00:30:11.332 --> 00:30:15.399
But I think his work is not always legal.

125
00:30:35.323 --> 00:30:39.148
Did you ever want to be
anything but a priest?

126
00:30:40.018 --> 00:30:43.763
Have you ever wanted to
be anything other than...

127
00:30:43.863 --> 00:30:44.820
...photographer?

128
00:30:44.920 --> 00:30:50.657
I do what I'm good at.
- You have the hands of a craftsman.

129
00:30:51.598 --> 00:30:55.168
Not an artist. You are good with machines.

130
00:30:56.707 --> 00:31:01.382
Yet you told me just the opposite
when we first met. Eh?

131
00:31:06.305 --> 00:31:10.061
Journalism can not make you a rich man.

132
00:31:13.504 --> 00:31:15.969
Perhaps you are rich already.

133
00:31:20.283 --> 00:31:26.019
A man can be rich if he
has God in his heart.

134
00:31:30.088 --> 00:31:34.338
I don't think God is very
interested in me. Father.

135
00:32:51.766 --> 00:32:54.895
Fabio.
Got some damage to my car.

136
00:32:56.564 --> 00:32:59.509
Sorry. I'm busy.
- I am the friend of...

137
00:32:59.609 --> 00:33:01.609
...father Benedetto.

138
00:33:01.886 --> 00:33:03.886
The American?
- Yes.

139
00:33:04.701 --> 00:33:08.101
I'm taking photographs to the mountains.

140
00:33:10.543 --> 00:33:12.543
Okey. okey.

141
00:33:21.704 --> 00:33:26.889
You need beautiful model for your photos.
Pretty Italian girl.

142
00:33:27.024 --> 00:33:30.594
No. I need tools for a broken drive shaft.

143
00:33:35.265 --> 00:33:38.707
Are you a mechanic?
- It's a hobby.

144
00:33:42.046 --> 00:33:45.800
My garage... your garage.

145
00:33:47.992 --> 00:33:51.987
However. you want to check a bit?
- Yes. thanks.

146
00:35:07.270 --> 00:35:10.085
How much?
- Nothing.

147
00:35:12.381 --> 00:35:14.381
Thank you.

148
00:37:59.595 --> 00:38:02.655
Where's Clara?
- Not working tonight.

149
00:38:03.665 --> 00:38:07.106
Want to drink anything?
- No. thanks.

150
00:38:07.210 --> 00:38:09.210
Thanks.

151
00:38:59.055 --> 00:39:01.350
Got a letter from a friend.

152
00:39:15.953 --> 00:39:20.543
Three dead in Dalarna

153
00:42:08.069 --> 00:42:10.069
Hello again.

154
00:43:04.816 --> 00:43:07.961
Is this place getting many visitors?.

155
00:43:08.154 --> 00:43:10.619
This is only way to get here.

156
00:43:11.806 --> 00:43:14.522
Did you check it for footprints
and tire tracks?

157
00:43:14.622 --> 00:43:18.447
Three days ago I walked
the river. Both sides.

158
00:43:18.795 --> 00:43:20.795
Let's check again.

159
00:44:29.519 --> 00:44:32.231
Rounds?
- I prepared two kinds.

160
00:44:32.440 --> 00:44:37.758
10 jacket and 10 expand.
- I'd like 20 of each.

161
00:44:38.907 --> 00:44:41.728
And then 10 explosive.
- Not a problem.

162
00:44:41.828 --> 00:44:45.738
Will mercury do?
- Mercury will do very nicely.

163
00:44:48.296 --> 00:44:50.336
I brought my own target.

164
00:44:58.831 --> 00:45:00.831
There.

165
00:45:45.668 --> 00:45:49.423
Muzzle velocity?
- About 360 miles an hour.

166
00:45:49.631 --> 00:45:54.227
That's including 20 miles an hour off
for the sound suppression.

167
00:45:54.327 --> 00:45:56.517
What model?
- M14.

168
00:45:57.768 --> 00:45:59.978
I've never had one before.

169
00:46:00.272 --> 00:46:02.272
You'll find it easy.

170
00:46:04.758 --> 00:46:06.904
I've rebalanced it by the
way due to suppressor.

171
00:46:07.004 --> 00:46:08.830
The fulcrum is 2 cm forward from the grip

172
00:46:08.930 --> 00:46:13.628
But that should not matter as I suppose
you'd fire it from a fixed position.

173
00:46:13.728 --> 00:46:14.984
There's no major recoil issues.

174
00:46:15.084 --> 00:46:19.844
You should be able to hold any
target. even the smallest.

175
00:46:50.447 --> 00:46:54.202
Go to the flower.
Fire into these reeds.

176
00:46:55.453 --> 00:46:57.663
Say two steps away for me.

177
00:46:58.896 --> 00:47:01.446
Two bursts.
Five seconds apart.

178
00:47:57.729 --> 00:48:03.849
The sound suppression is superb.
I could not place the direction of fire.

179
00:48:08.159 --> 00:48:10.980
I shall require the rounds and
the weapon by the first of next month.

180
00:48:11.080 --> 00:48:14.944
In the meantime. could you try adjusting
screws on the sight?. It's too loose.

181
00:48:15.044 --> 00:48:16.718
What about the case?

182
00:48:16.818 --> 00:48:18.744
It's a Samsonite briefcase. black.

183
00:48:18.844 --> 00:48:21.933
Combination locks it. Do you
have a number you prefer?

184
00:48:22.033 --> 00:48:24.120
014.
- 014.

185
00:48:27.979 --> 00:48:30.359
What should I do with these?

186
00:48:39.871 --> 00:48:41.871
How thoughtful.

187
00:48:43.627 --> 00:48:45.667
Asprinio. Don't know it.

188
00:48:45.713 --> 00:48:48.263
It's Muscatto. only frizzante.

189
00:48:48.425 --> 00:48:52.185
Wouldn't look good if.
the picnic wasn't touched.

190
00:48:52.285 --> 00:48:54.412
You chilled the wine.
- Had to be chilled.

191
00:48:54.512 --> 00:48:56.512
Italian cops.

192
00:49:02.508 --> 00:49:04.508
Do not move.

193
00:49:11.791 --> 00:49:13.791
So beautiful.

194
00:49:14.816 --> 00:49:16.816
It's endangered.

195
00:49:22.222 --> 00:49:25.792
You like coming here.
- Serves the purpose.

196
00:49:26.605 --> 00:49:29.007
You've never taken a woman here before?

197
00:49:29.107 --> 00:49:31.107
No.

198
00:49:37.140 --> 00:49:40.880
Perhaps you do not have a woman
in your life.

199
00:50:06.451 --> 00:50:09.936
Thank you for a lovely day. Mr Butterfly.

200
00:50:52.242 --> 00:50:54.848
Sergio Leone. Italian.

201
00:51:15.295 --> 00:51:17.295
No.

202
00:52:37.078 --> 00:52:39.078
Slowly. God.

203
00:53:59.262 --> 00:54:01.662
Everything is strange.

204
00:54:10.507 --> 00:54:12.507
Weird?

205
00:54:14.498 --> 00:54:16.498
Yes.

206
00:54:16.996 --> 00:54:18.252
It is as if...

207
00:54:18.352 --> 00:54:22.629
As if you can't stop
thinking about something.

208
00:54:27.469 --> 00:54:29.469
Or someone.

209
00:54:43.595 --> 00:54:45.595
Mr. Farfalla...

210
00:54:54.341 --> 00:54:56.341
You don't have to act.

211
00:54:57.469 --> 00:54:59.469
Act?

212
00:55:00.401 --> 00:55:04.359
You might have to with other clients but
you don't have to with me.

213
00:55:04.459 --> 00:55:06.967
I want you to be exactly who you are.

214
00:55:07.067 --> 00:55:10.722
I came here to get pleasure.
not to give it.

215
00:55:22.402 --> 00:55:24.782
Maybe I pretend very well...

216
00:55:33.668 --> 00:55:37.493
You give me my tips that the other girls get.

217
00:55:39.927 --> 00:55:42.647
I do not sleep with other girls.

218
00:57:38.321 --> 00:57:40.321
Hey. Mr. Farfalla.

219
00:57:40.407 --> 00:57:42.185
How are you?
- Okay. thanks.

220
00:57:42.285 --> 00:57:44.063
This is my girlfriend. Anna.

221
00:57:44.163 --> 00:57:45.522
Hi.

222
00:57:45.622 --> 00:57:47.505
Nice to meet you. Anna.

223
00:57:47.605 --> 00:57:50.530
You want to join me for some coffee?

224
00:57:50.630 --> 00:57:52.615
No. go see an American movie.

225
00:57:52.715 --> 00:57:54.598
Anna is learning English.

226
00:57:54.698 --> 00:57:57.248
I would love to go to America.

227
00:57:58.974 --> 00:58:04.501
But perhaps we can see each other soon.
On Wednesday I'm free.

228
00:58:05.232 --> 00:58:07.232
OK. I'll be there.

229
00:58:07.840 --> 00:58:09.840
Where?

230
00:58:10.761 --> 00:58:12.761
The usual place.

231
00:58:14.515 --> 00:58:19.102
The usual place. I forgot.
Where is our usual place?

232
00:58:28.489 --> 00:58:30.489
Let's go someplace new.

233
00:58:31.827 --> 00:58:33.827
You can decide.

234
00:58:36.729 --> 00:58:39.024
Locanda Grappalli?
- Great.

235
00:58:39.337 --> 00:58:41.637
Locanda Grappalli - good food.

236
00:58:41.737 --> 00:58:43.862
Grappali?
- See you there?

237
00:58:44.346 --> 00:58:46.534
See you there.
- At 8.

238
00:58:46.847 --> 00:58:48.847
8.

239
00:58:49.768 --> 00:58:51.768
Goodbye. Mr. Farfalla.

240
00:58:52.376 --> 00:58:54.841
Anna. I was nice to meet you.

241
00:59:18.346 --> 00:59:21.581
Two more murdered prostitutes.

242
01:03:08.649 --> 01:03:09.801
Yes.

243
01:03:09.901 --> 01:03:11.262
The Swedes found me.

244
01:03:11.362 --> 01:03:13.362
Stay put.

245
01:03:13.656 --> 01:03:15.656
Finish the job.

246
01:03:15.742 --> 01:03:18.458
How the fuck did they know I was here?

247
01:03:18.558 --> 01:03:21.448
Cause you've lost your edge. Jack.

248
01:04:07.499 --> 01:04:10.644
Some are greater sinners than others.

249
01:04:43.150 --> 01:04:46.382
Good morning. You're up early.

250
01:04:46.695 --> 01:04:48.695
I needed some air.

251
01:04:50.241 --> 01:04:52.281
I walk here to meditate.

252
01:04:52.642 --> 01:04:55.665
I thank God for certain favors...

253
01:04:56.396 --> 01:04:58.396
...he has granted me.

254
01:04:58.795 --> 01:05:02.346
And ask him to look after
to those of my friends...

255
01:05:02.446 --> 01:05:04.446
...who are sinners

256
01:05:07.868 --> 01:05:09.868
All men are sinners.

257
01:05:12.980 --> 01:05:17.740
But those who seek peace
are much sinning in the history.

258
01:05:18.195 --> 01:05:20.077
Maybe.

259
01:05:20.177 --> 01:05:24.172
Forgive me. this is the priest
in me speaking...

260
01:05:24.245 --> 01:05:28.625
...but you have done
much sinning. Mr. Clark.

261
01:05:30.607 --> 01:05:33.737
Are you still do.

262
01:05:37.177 --> 01:05:40.152
Something happened here last night.

263
01:05:41.454 --> 01:05:44.172
Everything I've done I
had good cause to do.

264
01:05:44.272 --> 01:05:45.735
Do you wish to tell me?

265
01:05:45.835 --> 01:05:47.835
To confess?
- Yes.

266
01:05:48.339 --> 01:05:49.803
For what reason?

267
01:05:49.903 --> 01:05:51.903
For your sake.

268
01:05:52.094 --> 01:05:55.239
Perhaps I can pray for you.
- perhaps.

269
01:05:57.204 --> 01:06:01.168
I wonder how many bastards
have been made here

270
01:06:04.403 --> 01:06:06.403
You work in metal...

271
01:06:06.904 --> 01:06:10.049
You were given some steel by Fabio...

272
01:06:10.138 --> 01:06:12.138
The car doctor.

273
01:06:13.580 --> 01:06:16.215
Where was he conceived. Father?

274
01:06:16.292 --> 01:06:18.292
Fabio Tacardato...

275
01:06:18.796 --> 01:06:20.796
Why do you ask me that?

276
01:06:21.924 --> 01:06:24.015
You have each others photos.

277
01:06:24.115 --> 01:06:26.410
You have each other's eyes.

278
01:06:27.244 --> 01:06:33.534
Was he conceived here under the trees
at night like all the other bastards?

279
01:06:34.129 --> 01:06:36.214
I do not remember. sir.

280
01:06:38.405 --> 01:06:40.405
It was many years ago.

281
01:06:44.767 --> 01:06:48.252
In the end. it is I who confesses to you.

282
01:06:48.626 --> 01:06:50.404
You want me to do the same?

283
01:06:50.504 --> 01:06:52.504
For your own good.

284
01:06:52.590 --> 01:06:55.515
You can not doubt the existence of hell.

285
01:06:55.615 --> 01:06:57.497
You live in it.

286
01:06:57.597 --> 01:06:59.892
It is a place without love.

287
01:07:01.248 --> 01:07:04.277
Perhaps I don't have the right
to wear these robes...

288
01:07:04.377 --> 01:07:06.377
But I have a heart...

289
01:07:06.983 --> 01:07:09.178
...full of a father's love.

290
01:07:09.278 --> 01:07:12.721
Something close to his heart.

291
01:07:15.328 --> 01:07:18.898
And for that. I'm both grateful and happy.

292
01:07:24.298 --> 01:07:26.298
What do you have?

293
01:07:27.949 --> 01:07:29.949
My friend?

294
01:08:13.634 --> 01:08:15.634
On time.

295
01:08:17.806 --> 01:08:21.291
I was not sure. you know.
you were coming.

296
01:08:21.353 --> 01:08:23.988
I was not sure you meant me to.

297
01:08:24.168 --> 01:08:26.168
Of course yes.

298
01:08:31.157 --> 01:08:33.537
Good evening.
- Good evening.

299
01:08:41.170 --> 01:08:43.679
Can you bring us a bottle
of mineral water and a Montepulciano?

300
01:08:43.779 --> 01:08:45.779
English menu?

301
01:08:46.072 --> 01:08:47.015
No. thanks.

302
01:08:47.115 --> 01:08:48.580
German. Dutch?

303
01:08:48.680 --> 01:08:50.145
Gentleman speaks Italian as good as me.

304
01:08:50.245 --> 01:08:56.620
I repeat: a bottle of mineral water
and a bottle of Montepulciano d'Abruzzo.

305
01:08:56.917 --> 01:08:59.108
With gas?
- No

306
01:09:02.553 --> 01:09:04.933
People from the provinces...

307
01:09:20.702 --> 01:09:22.270
Can I ask you something?

308
01:09:22.370 --> 01:09:24.370
Sure.

309
01:09:27.793 --> 01:09:29.793
You're married?

310
01:09:31.340 --> 01:09:33.340
No.

311
01:09:36.450 --> 01:09:39.063
I was sure this was your secret.

312
01:09:39.163 --> 01:09:41.798
Why do I have to have a secret?

313
01:09:44.169 --> 01:09:47.924
You're a good man. but...
You are a secret.

314
01:09:54.079 --> 01:09:54.813
Excuse me.

315
01:09:54.913 --> 01:09:56.963
No. No. thanks.

316
01:09:56.998 --> 01:09:59.973
No. He thinks that we are a couple.

317
01:10:01.380 --> 01:10:03.675
It's all right.
- Thank you.

318
01:14:31.840 --> 01:14:33.840
Hello.

319
01:14:33.926 --> 01:14:35.926
I need some more time.

320
01:14:37.055 --> 01:14:39.350
You're testing my patience.

321
01:14:39.975 --> 01:14:42.440
Just give me a few more days.

322
01:14:44.356 --> 01:14:47.671
You have two days.
Then you make a drop.

323
01:15:33.797 --> 01:15:35.881
Hi.
- Hi.

324
01:15:45.164 --> 01:15:47.164
Where we go?

325
01:15:47.250 --> 01:15:49.133
Someplace beautiful.

326
01:15:49.233 --> 01:15:51.233
We go to a picnic?

327
01:15:55.176 --> 01:15:57.216
Picnic.
- Yeah. a picnic.

328
01:15:58.515 --> 01:16:01.065
I have to practice my English.

329
01:16:01.228 --> 01:16:04.773
Today we're going to have a picnic.

330
01:16:04.878 --> 01:16:06.878
It is a beautiful day.

331
01:16:37.839 --> 01:16:41.698
Where are we going?
- You'll see.

332
01:16:51.293 --> 01:16:54.843
I think it is good we stay close to the road.

333
01:16:54.943 --> 01:17:00.638
Don't worry. I've been down
this road many times taking photographs.

334
01:17:14.554 --> 01:17:17.682
Only you come here?
- Yes.

335
01:17:33.433 --> 01:17:35.433
It is a paradise.

336
01:17:47.617 --> 01:17:50.437
I'm going to swim in the water.
You come?

337
01:17:50.537 --> 01:17:52.537
It is cold.

338
01:17:53.981 --> 01:17:55.981
Maybe.

339
01:18:05.140 --> 01:18:07.140
Come.

340
01:18:10.565 --> 01:18:12.565
Come. Mr. Farfalla.

341
01:18:13.798 --> 01:18:15.798
Is beautiful. no?

342
01:18:22.664 --> 01:18:24.704
We make love in water...

343
01:18:30.800 --> 01:18:32.800
What is wrong?
339

344
01:18:32.989 --> 01:18:34.989
Should eat.

345
01:18:39.769 --> 01:18:41.769
Look. It's a bullet.

346
01:18:42.273 --> 01:18:43.946
Maybe there are hunters here.

347
01:18:44.046 --> 01:18:46.046
I don't think so.

348
01:19:18.257 --> 01:19:23.577
Edward... is it your real name?

349
01:19:47.150 --> 01:19:49.190
Can you put this behind?

350
01:19:53.929 --> 01:19:55.929
What?

351
01:19:58.831 --> 01:20:00.831
What?

352
01:20:06.654 --> 01:20:08.654
Nothing.

353
01:20:23.134 --> 01:20:24.781
Grazie
- ust don't understand what the...

354
01:20:24.881 --> 01:20:26.163
...hell are you doing with a gun.

355
01:20:26.263 --> 01:20:28.041
A friend of mine gave it to me.

356
01:20:28.141 --> 01:20:30.857
The two prostitutes
were killed in Pescara. right?

357
01:20:30.957 --> 01:20:33.047
Did you see what they do to them?

358
01:20:33.147 --> 01:20:34.507
The police showed me the photographs.

359
01:20:34.607 --> 01:20:36.003
I wanted to feel safe with clients.

360
01:20:36.103 --> 01:20:37.845
Does it make you feel safe with me?

361
01:20:37.945 --> 01:20:39.410
You're not a client.

362
01:20:39.510 --> 01:20:43.930
Then why is it in your bag?
- Because I work tonight.

363
01:20:56.928 --> 01:20:58.928
It is a 'procession'.

364
01:20:59.849 --> 01:21:03.917
A procession?
- Yes. Tomorrow

365
01:21:08.506 --> 01:21:10.631
Want to do this together?

366
01:21:11.740 --> 01:21:13.622
Maybe.

367
01:21:13.722 --> 01:21:15.722
Really?

368
01:21:17.059 --> 01:21:22.379
And after? After that.
tomorrow. the next day...

369
01:21:23.526 --> 01:21:26.076
I can not stay forever. Clara.

370
01:21:35.833 --> 01:21:37.857
It's time to go.
- Take me home with you.

371
01:21:37.957 --> 01:21:40.214
I can't.

372
01:22:30.071 --> 01:22:32.071
Yeah?

373
01:22:32.576 --> 01:22:33.643
I'll make the delivery.
then I'm out.

374
01:22:33.743 --> 01:22:35.743
Hello?

375
01:22:39.459 --> 01:22:41.459
Palo?

376
01:22:46.238 --> 01:22:47.078
Okay. Jack.

377
01:22:47.178 --> 01:22:49.178
You're out

378
01:23:30.047 --> 01:23:32.852
Now you listen to me carefully...

379
01:26:25.067 --> 01:26:27.067
A coffee.

380
01:26:40.714 --> 01:26:42.908
I see you've brought it in with you.

381
01:26:43.008 --> 01:26:45.620
Everything is here. as we agreed.

382
01:26:45.720 --> 01:26:47.720
What is this?

383
01:26:48.433 --> 01:26:50.433
Candy for your trip.

384
01:26:55.003 --> 01:26:58.549
Thought you might have a sweet tooth.

385
01:27:02.931 --> 01:27:04.971
That's very kind of you.

386
01:27:14.299 --> 01:27:18.464
I guess I'll be reading about it
in the 'Tribune'?

387
01:27:21.600 --> 01:27:23.686
Yes. I expect so.

388
01:27:30.131 --> 01:27:32.131
Two.

389
01:27:43.818 --> 01:27:47.218
I'm just going to the ladies. Wait here.

390
01:28:52.553 --> 01:28:54.743
You okay?
- I'm fine. You?

391
01:28:55.160 --> 01:28:57.042
Just fine.

392
01:28:57.142 --> 01:28:59.142
You won't need a gun.

393
01:28:59.333 --> 01:29:01.333
You never know.

394
01:29:15.083 --> 01:29:17.083
Final payment.

395
01:29:22.071 --> 01:29:24.791
Buy yourself a retirement clock.

396
01:29:49.816 --> 01:29:51.816
Goodbye. Mr. Butterfly.

397
01:30:45.932 --> 01:30:47.500
Hello?

398
01:30:47.600 --> 01:30:49.378
What happened?

399
01:30:49.478 --> 01:30:51.943
There wasn't any opportunity.

400
01:30:52.503 --> 01:30:54.280
Find one.

401
01:30:54.380 --> 01:30:56.380
I'm following it now.

402
01:32:49.636 --> 01:32:51.636
I was looking for you.

403
01:32:52.869 --> 01:32:54.869
I'm here.

404
01:32:55.268 --> 01:32:57.254
What are you doing tonight?

405
01:32:57.354 --> 01:32:59.354
I work tonight.

406
01:32:59.858 --> 01:33:01.858
Don't.

407
01:33:06.011 --> 01:33:09.249
If I ask you to come
away with me. would you?

408
01:33:09.349 --> 01:33:11.349
Come away with you?

409
01:33:12.583 --> 01:33:14.583
Why not?

410
01:33:19.780 --> 01:33:21.662
Together?
- Together.

411
01:33:21.762 --> 01:33:24.056
Forever?
- Forever.

412
01:33:38.241 --> 01:33:41.479
I want you to take this and
meet me at the river.

413
01:33:41.579 --> 01:33:43.579
Eduardo?
- Go. Go.

414
01:34:05.875 --> 01:34:07.875
Who do you work for?

415
01:34:09.423 --> 01:34:11.423
Who?

416
01:34:11.613 --> 01:34:13.613
For the same man...

417
01:34:17.245 --> 01:34:18.917
...as you Jack.

418
01:34:19.017 --> 01:34:21.017
Yes

419
01:34:44.365 --> 01:34:46.365
I'm sorry. Father.

420
01:38:59.909 --> 01:39:01.909
Eduardo.

421
01:39:01.994 --> 01:39:03.876
Eduardo.

422
01:39:03.976 --> 01:39:05.976
Eduardo.
